==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Complin
<hw>Com"plin</hw> }</mhw> <pr>(?)</pr>,
<pos>n.</pos> <ety>[From OE. <ets>complie</ets>, OF. <ets>complie</ets>,
F. <ets>complies</ets>, pl., fr. LL. <ets>completa</ets> (prop. fem. of
L. <ets>completus</ets>) the religious exercise which completes and
closes the service of the day. See <er>Complete</er>.]</ety>
<fld>(Eccl.)</fld> <def>The last division of the Roman Catholic
breviary; the seventh and last of the canonical hours of the Western
church; the last prayer of the day, to be said after sunset.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The custom of godly man been to shut up the evening with a
<qex>compline</qex> of prayer at nine of the night.</q>
<rj><qau>Hammond.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Complot</ent>⟦br⟧
